# Copy the Electron entry HTML from frontend/ up into the build variant root
# so the renderer can `loadFile(index.html)` (paths inside index.html are
# resolved relative to the variant root).  `!tup_preserve` copies a source
# file into the variant tree; it works on every platform — Windows included,
# see the resource Tupfiles under public/resources/* — so these rules are no
# longer gated behind `ifneq win32`.  Note the input/output relative paths
# must differ (frontend/index.html -> index.html): a same-relative-path
# `!tup_preserve` from this parent Tupfile triggers a Tup "generated node
# already exists as a normal file" conflict against the variant-mirrored
# source copy.  The default config/layout files therefore need no rule here —
# they already reach build-debug/config/ via the variant source mirror.
: frontend/index.html |> !tup_preserve |> index.html
: frontend/subwindow.html |> !tup_preserve |> subwindow.html
